Overview

Hirehood is a one-stop-shop, online platform that allows you to hire items from local businesses in your area or where you are lucky enough to be holidaying. Its marketplace-style platform lists items for hire from local operators. Consumers can hire a variety of items at once with just a few clicks of a button.

The company also has a booking system for vendors to help support inventory management and manage bookings and payments. This helps its vendors re-target customers in the future. Hirehood has many positive environmental and social benefits by helping reduce the need to purchase items and connecting communities.

The Problem

Travelling with bulky items when going on holidays is a tedious and stress-inducing task that many people, in particular those with young children, would prefer to avoid.

And, many hire businesses have outdated practices with labour-intensive booking and inventory management systems.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The Solution

On the customer side, this problem can be solved by bringing hire businesses onto a single digital platform, making it easier for people to hire the things they need.

On the vendor side, Hirehood has also built its own booking management system for suppliers to help them digitise their businesses and help manage availability, bookings and payments online.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Competitive Advantage

Hirehood is the first platform of its kind in Australia. Built on partnerships with local accommodation providers and suppliers who love the one-stop-shop model as a way to enhance customers' holiday experiences, the company is already well ahead in terms of its testing, traction and development making it difficult for other competitors to catch up.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Traction

Hirehood is an early-stage start-up, excited to provide its community with the opportunity to invest in an innovative local start-up that almost all Australians can relate to and also use for themselves when travelling.

The summer holidays have certainly seen an increase in both customers and users.

Since launching in August 2023, the company has seen its customer base increase on average 20% MoM, with bookings through its platform quite similar.

80% of the suppliers they have approached have been instantly excited and joined the platform to list their items for hire.

The company has also gained a higher-than-expected number of referral sources from its demand side, with over 200 Airbnbs, caravan parks, hotels and resorts sharing its QR code booking system either digitally or physically with guests. Hirehood is seeing an increased amount of accommodation providers in different areas proactively reach out to the team and further funding will help the company scale its supply to these areas to meet demand.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Market Opportunity

In terms of hire shops Hirehood is targeting to list on its platform, there are approximately 10,000 holiday-style hire businesses in Australia and an estimated 1.26 million worldwide.

In terms of users, in 2022, Australians travelled domestically for 74 million visitor days and they spent a further 44 million days visiting friends or family.

Over 5.4 million tourists visited Australia from overseas in 2023. This was above 8 million in the year before Covid.

The global consumer goods and general rental centres market is expected to grow to $229.6 billion by 2027 with a CAGR of 7.7%. Recreational goods such as baby equipment, bikes, kayaks and camping gear fall into this grouping.*

*sources: The Business Research Company

Valuation Today & Valuation Uplift

By continuing to raise at higher valuations to support the growth of the below.

  • Hire Businesses: From Zero to ~2000 within 5 years
  • Listed Items for Hire: From Zero to ~20,000 in 5 years (Based on an average of 10 items listed per business)
  • Total Number of Hires: From Zero to 600,000 in 5 years (Based on each item being hired out once bi-monthly)
  • Overall Business Revenue: From Zero to $2,400,000 in 5 years

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Financials

The current financial year ‘23/24 remains an investment year with a projected EBITDA loss of just over $500k (representing a strong investment in scaling the growth drivers that have already been tested and proved out).

The next financial year ‘24/25 is projected to be break even. The financial years that follow are projected to be strong profit years, where we are able to fund the ongoing rapid growth of the business from the profits generated.

Growth expectations – forecast revenue of $650K in FY24 increasing to $7.65 million in FY26, at 55% gross margin.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Exit Strategy

There is a strong track record of recreational rental company acquisitions in the tourism sector. At the moment, Hirehood is focused on building its platform, but both IPO and acquisition would be options for the future.
